  "special": {
    "title": "Hand over the keys, Sugar...",
    "description": "Always Slag. Very low base damage and very high slag application. While held: 65% lifesteal on all damage you deal. Projectile behaviour: slow shots that detonate three times in flight. Two mid-air blasts at 0.6s and 1.2s deal 50% bullet damage in an area; a final blast at 2.0s deals 80% bullet damage with 60% increased radius. Crit: +400% critical damage. Drunk: every 5s, 13% chance to intoxicate you for 5s. While drunk: +5 projectiles, -50% fire rate, worse accuracy, swaying view. Persists through weapon swaps; swapping resets the 5s check. Known issue: magazine is 2 larger than shown."
  },
  "notes": "Normally it cannot be kept outside the quest, though it has been available briefly as a special event drop. The drunken state can carry over after swapping weapons; swapping can also refresh the internal timer and let it trigger sooner. Grenade damage boosts can increase its damage. Damage dealt by separate entities such as Axton's Sabre Turret does not return healing. Damaging objects with health bars (for example barrels or fuse boxes) can still heal you. The true magazine size is always 2 rounds higher than the card value.",
